      <title>HACKERS RUINING THE GAME</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12124#M12124</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;We all see Hacking on a daily basis. Not only is there Show_EQ, ghosting, and other exploits. Zek is now the proud owner of “characters that do not take any damage” “people that can not be mezzed or stunned” “people that can warp on top of you from the other side of the zone” “people that can not be hit by melee damage” “tracking casters” and even “succoring rangers.”&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;When you petition GMs say they must either witness the hacking/exploiting or you must use the /report command. When you are being spammed by hackers 15-20 lines of text is usually not enough to catch the offence. If GMs would simply walk around, watch some pvp fights or go to zones like Crypt of Nadox, PoV, PoF where it is common to find level 70 warriors using the Earthshaker / Disc exploit to kill the whole zone while powerleveling a group of people, they could witness the cheating first hand. The Earthshaker exploit is so common now that people “WTB (Earthshaker) ES Pulls” in general chat. Once again people are getting exp by sitting around doing nothing. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;I know there are potions, call of hero, divine aura, and other tricks that may appear to be hacks when they really aren’t. But the hacking on Zek is so obvious that it can not be any form of legitimate trickery. It’s gotten to the point where people do not even deny hacking, of course they don’t admit it either.&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;I don’t remember hacking/exploiting being this bad on blue servers. If someone did something minimal like steal your mob or train you, a GM would come down and say something. On Zek people are hacking like crazy and not much (if anything) is being done about it. And no I don’t want to go back to a blue server, I just want to be on a pvp server where cheating is the exception and not the norm. &lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
