      <title>Re: HACKERS RUINING THE GAME</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12222#M12222</link>
      <description>I have to heartily disagree with anyone calling Earthshaker&#xD;
powerleveling a blatant exploit. I think it's an old piece of&#xD;
player-crafted technique content that should be left in.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
In cases where it has caused problems, I would have to agree with the&#xD;
way GMs have handled it, when they've actually chosen to intervene to&#xD;
do so. As far as I've witnessed this means leaving ES pullers alone&#xD;
most of the time, but if an ES puller decides to train and kill Plane&#xD;
of Valor while several groups are trying to straight exp off the same&#xD;
mobs, then suspending and/or banning the ES puller for zone disruption.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
I think ES pulling is harmless as long as it doesn't interfere with&#xD;
normal grind experience, etc. Once it starts interfering with that&#xD;
you're coming closer to an early DoD style universe in which the only&#xD;
highly acceptable forms of experience are paid for, and let's face it,&#xD;
that's not what the intent of the games' designers was. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
In my opinion, don't remove the content or ban its users, simply make&#xD;
it clear that this kind of niche powerleveling must be performed&#xD;
without the disruption or harassment of players who aren't choosing to&#xD;
partake in it.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
As far as greater hacking exploits are concerned, I think Hotmix&#xD;
touched on a very real, longstanding, broader concern: GM effectiveness&#xD;
where issues that are difficult to /report are concerned.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Not only do GMs almost always request a /report for hacking&#xD;
accusations, but also for plain 'ole harassment and disruption reports,&#xD;
such as training, etc. It is extremely hard to capture an effective&#xD;
report to this end. I haven't seen any trainers enter a zone and /ooc&#xD;
HEY IM GONNA TRAIN YOU TO HARASS YOU NOW recently. I doubt you have,&#xD;
either. The best you're likely to get is to the effect of.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
trainerdude says out of character 'inc train'&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
you say out of character '**SMURF**? **SMURF**'&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
trainerdude's trained mob hits YOU for 834438943 points of damage&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
trainerdude's trained mob hits YOU for 834438943 points of damage&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
trainerdude's trained mob hits YOU for 834438943 points of damage&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
trainerdude's trained mob hits YOU for 834438943 points of damage&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
trainerdude's trained mob hits YOU for 834438943 points of damage&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
you have been slain by trainerdude's trained mob! returning to bind point&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
please wait...&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
And you're not even going to get those helpful indicative labels for&#xD;
the mobs. In the end, all you'll get is a GM contacting trainerdude and&#xD;
trainerdude saying the train was accidental and a result of botched&#xD;
exploration in the zone or something similar. The same is true&#xD;
reporting hackers, they're not going to be admitting to hacking, and&#xD;
/reporting chat as proof of something someone wishes to conceal is&#xD;
nearly impossible. &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Either GMs need to commit some active patrolling of PvP and exp-heavy&#xD;
zones, or they need to find a quick and easy way to parse logs to&#xD;
detect hacking, harassment, etc. Until they do we'll be doomed to&#xD;
submitting utterly useless, non-revelatory reports that don't **SMURF** any&#xD;
of the offenders whatsoever and to facing the fact there really is no&#xD;
effective system in place by which harassment and hacking can be&#xD;
reported and dealt with.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
And please, if you don't play the PvP server, or maintain an&#xD;
antagonistic attitude towards it, don't enter this board and trash on&#xD;
it. We play here, most of us would never consider playing anywhere&#xD;
else, most of us hate you&amp;nbsp; just as much as you hate us, so stay&#xD;
where you belong and let us try to provide valuable feedback here in&#xD;
the hopes of working out the kinks on our server. You all get a new one&#xD;
on June 28th. We don't, so we're trying to fix the one we have.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
