      <description>&lt;div&gt;My sense is that they don't really care.  EQ is a game in decline.  Its peak subscribership was long ago.  For Sony, it's all about riding this gravy train until it pulls into the station now.  That means not spending a lot on new development, and putting what development effort they are still willing to invest in it into the things that are going to generate revenue (like new expansions).  The unfortunate reality is that putting more GMs on Zek to observe people doing these things isn't a money maker.  Neither is addressing the structural issues that make the PVP system so screwey (see the top ten issues post by Pinhead) right now.  Don't expect that to change anytime soon.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We've all been ganked by the player who seems to be able to gate, and succor, and track when their class shouldn't have those abilities.  Yeah, it sucks, but it's been going on for years.  Its obvious that SOE either can't stop it, or, more likely, they aren't interested enough to spend the money that it would take to stop it.  You'd probably just accept that it's a reality of everquest PVP.  About all you can do is vote with your feet and play some other game (or on a non-PVP server) if it bothers you that much.  Lets not forget that it's a game, and games are supposed to be fun.  When it stops being fun, it's time to do something else.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
